  138. let[@inline] min (x: float) (y: float) =
  139.   if y > x || (not(sign_bit y) && sign_bit x) then
  140.     if is_nan y then y else x
  141.   else if is_nan x then x else y

  143. let[@inline] max (x: float) (y: float) =
  144.   if y > x || (not(sign_bit y) && sign_bit x) then
  145.     if is_nan x then x else y
  146.   else if is_nan y then y else x

  148. let[@inline] min_max (x: float) (y: float) =
  149.   if is_nan x || is_nan y then (nan, nan)
  150.   else if y > x || (not(sign_bit y) && sign_bit x) then (x, y) else (y, x)

  152. let[@inline] min_num (x: float) (y: float) =
  153.   if y > x || (not(sign_bit y) && sign_bit x) then
  154.     if is_nan x then y else x
  155.   else if is_nan y then x else y

  157. let[@inline] max_num (x: float) (y: float) =
  158.   if y > x || (not(sign_bit y) && sign_bit x) then

  162. let[@inline] min_max_num (x: float) (y: float) =

  183.   let unsafe_fill a ofs len v =
  184.     for i = ofs to ofs + len - 1 do unsafe_set a i v done

  186.   external unsafe_blit: t -> int -> t -> int -> int -> unit =
  187.     "caml_floatarray_blit" [@@noalloc]

  189.   let check a ofs len msg =
  190.     if ofs < 0 || len < 0 || ofs + len < 0 || ofs + len > length a then
  191.       invalid_arg msg

  193.   let make n v =
  194.     let result = create n in
  195.     unsafe_fill result 0 n v;
  196.     result

  198.   let init l f =
  199.     if l < 0 then invalid_arg "Float.Array.init"
  200.     else
  201.       let res = create l in

  203.         unsafe_set res i (f i)
  204.       done;
  205.       res

  207.   let append a1 a2 =

  209.     let l2 = length a2 in
  210.     let result = create (l1 + l2) in

  216.   let ensure_ge (x:int) y =
  217.     if x >= y then x else invalid_arg "Float.Array.concat"

  219.   let rec sum_lengths acc = function
  220.     | [] -> acc
  221.     | hd :: tl -> sum_lengths (ensure_ge (length hd + acc) acc) tl

  223.   let concat l =
  224.     let len = sum_lengths 0 l in
  225.     let result = create len in
  226.     let rec loop l i =
  227.       match l with
  228.       | [] -> assert (i = len)
  229.       | hd :: tl ->
  230.         let hlen = length hd in
  231.         unsafe_blit hd 0 result i hlen;
  232.         loop tl (i + hlen)
  233.     in
  234.     loop l 0;
  235.     result

  237.   let sub a ofs len =

  241.     result

  243.   let copy a =

  247.     result

  249.   let fill a ofs len v =

  253.   let blit src sofs dst dofs len =

  258.   let to_list a =
